Weather Forecast Command Line App (Python)
A simple command line application built using Python that fetches real time weather data for any city using the OpenWeatherMap API.

Features
Takes city name as user input
Displays temperature in Celsius
Shows weather condition, humidity, and wind speed
Handles invalid city names gracefully
Uses only built-in Python libraries

Tech Stack
Python
urllib.request
json
OpenWeatherMap API

How It Works
User enters a city name.
The program sends a request to the OpenWeatherMap API.
Weather data is fetched in JSON format.
The data is parsed and displayed in a readable format.
